{"log_type": "agent_output", "timestamp_iso": "2026-03-20T09:58:33", "timestamp_unix": 1774018713, "data": {"type": "result", "subtype": "success", "is_error": false, "duration_ms": 526419, "duration_api_ms": 527926, "num_turns": 39, "result": "Now I have the exact source. Let me analyze the root cause:\n\n> [THOUGHT]\n> **Root Cause Analysis:**\n> - Line 137: `ret->content = (xmlChar *) xmlMallocAtomic(ret->size * sizeof(xmlChar));`\n> - Line 143: `ret->content[0] = 0;` \u2014 only byte 0 is initialized; bytes `1..size-1` remain uninitialized\n> - The MSAN origin trace confirms: `malloc` at `buf.c:137` \u2192 `realloc` at `buf.c:486` (uninitialized bytes propagate through `xmlBufGrowInternal`) \u2192 uninitialized read in `xmlNextChar` at `parserInternals.c:526`\n> - **Fix**: Replace `xmlMallocAtomic` with `xmlCalloc(ret->size, sizeof(xmlChar))` in `xmlBufCreate` to zero-initialize the entire content buffer\n> - Note: `xmlBufCreateSize` at line 172 has the identical pattern but is not in the crash trace \u2014 fixing only the confirmed origin per minimal-invasiveness principle\n>\n> **Confidence: 98%** \u2014 crash trace is unambiguous; fix is a 1-line change from `malloc` to `calloc`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"PATCH_READY\",\n  \"patches\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"buf.c\",\n      \"diff\": \"--- a/buf.c\\n+++ b/buf.c\\n@@ -134,7 +134,7 @@\\n     ret->size = xmlDefaultBufferSize;\\n     ret->compat_size = xmlDefaultBufferSize;\\n     ret->alloc = xmlBufferAllocScheme;\\n-    ret->content = (xmlChar *) xmlMallocAtomic(ret->size * sizeof(xmlChar));\\n+    ret->content = (xmlChar *) xmlCalloc(ret->size, sizeof(xmlChar));\\n     if (ret->content == NULL) {\\n \\txmlBufMemoryError(ret, \\\"creating buffer\\\");\\n \\txmlFree(ret);\\n\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary of the fix:**\n\n| | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **File** | `buf.c` |\n| **Function** | `xmlBufCreate` |\n| **Line** | 137 |\n| **Root cause** | `xmlMallocAtomic` allocates `xmlDefaultBufferSize` bytes without initialization. Only `content[0]` is set to `0`; bytes `1..size-1` remain uninitialized. When `xmlBufGrowInternal` later calls `realloc`, MSAN propagates these uninitialized bytes into the grown buffer, which `xmlNextChar` eventually reads. |\n| **Fix** | Replace `xmlMallocAtomic(ret->size * sizeof(xmlChar))` with `xmlCalloc(ret->size, sizeof(xmlChar))`. `xmlCalloc` is `calloc`-based and zero-initializes all allocated bytes, eliminating the uninitialized-value origin at the allocation site. |\n| **Invasiveness** | Single-line change; no logic, structure, or API changes. |", "stop_reason": null, "session_id": "05b8371f-60e1-4566-a1de-2c0ccf0e1bc5", "total_cost_usd": 1.4236990000000005, "usage": {"input_tokens": 124, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 32117, "cache_read_input_tokens": 1045016, "output_tokens": 22968, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 32117, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}, "modelUsage": {"claude-sonnet-4-6": {"inputTokens": 132, "outputTokens": 23830, "cacheReadInputTokens": 1080349, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 45422, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 1.4204720000000006, "contextWindow": 200000, "maxOutputTokens": 32000}, "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001": {"inputTokens": 2267, "outputTokens": 192, "cacheReadInputTokens": 0, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 0, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.003227, "contextWindow": 200000, "maxOutputTokens": 32000}}, "permission_denials": [{"tool_name": "Bash", "tool_use_id": "toolu_01JGGuKFGEfe3i1iucFM39z3", "tool_input": {"command": "docker exec vulnscan sed -n '120,160p' /src/libxml2/buf.c", "description": "Read xmlBufCreate around line 137 in buf.c"}}, {"tool_name": "Bash", "tool_use_id": "toolu_01SmN52tovpiJ75HVyb1gxJy", "tool_input": {"command": "docker exec vulnscan ls /src/libxml2/", "description": "List libxml2 source files in con